 This is a quick setup guide to create secure confluent kafka setup for Demo and personal use using Docker. 
 This setup support both SSL and SASL based authentication with client via MTLS.


Architecture:

┌─────────────┐    mTLS (port 9093)    ┌──────────────────────────┐
│   Client    │◄──────────────────────►│   Kafka Broker           │
│ client.crt  │   Both sides verify    │   broker.crt             │
│ client.key  │   each other's cert    │   kafka.keystore.jks     │
└─────────────┘                        └──────────────────────────┘
       │                                           │
       └─────────── Signed by same CA ─────────────┘
                       ca.crt / ca.key

To verfiy the setup KAFKA IO is used to verify if kafka is configured successfully.
can be downloaded from https://kafkio.com/

Directory structure:
Confluent-kafka/
├── docker-compose.yml          # Confluent Kafka + ZooKeeper + Schema Registry
├── certs/                      # All certificates (generated by script)
│   ├── ca.crt                  # Certificate Authority (public)
│   ├── ca.key                  # CA private key (keep secret!)
│   ├── broker.crt              # Broker certificate
│   ├── broker.key              # Broker private key
│   ├── client.crt              # Client certificate
│   ├── client.key              # Client private key
│   ├── client-combined.pem     # client.crt + client.key combined
│   ├── kafka.keystore.jks      # Broker keystore (JKS)
│   ├── kafka.truststore.jks    # Broker truststore (JKS)
│   ├── keystore_creds          # Keystore password file
│   └── truststore_creds        # Truststore password file
├── config/
│   └── kafka_server_jaas.conf 
│   └── kafka-ui.yml            
│   └── zookeeper_jaas.conf   
└── scripts/
    └── generate-certs.sh       # Certificate generation script

1.How to start?
Download the code https://github.com/Amit008/Confluent-kafka.git
execute thecommand from directory: Confluent-kafka>docker compose up -d




